    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Edward Berman was an American author and professor of economics at the University of Illinois, specializing inlabor economics.  He is the author of several books and scholarly articles, and was for a time the editor of <emph render="italic">The American Economic Review</emph>.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Edward Berman Letters</emph> consist of incoming correspondence from insurance companies and others, concerning Berman's book, <emph render="italic">Life insurance: a critical examination</emph>.</p>
    </scopecontent>
